  <refnamediv>
    <refname>integralKernel</refname>
    <refpurpose>This function creates a filter to be used with integral images.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   results = intergralKernel(bbox, weight);
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>results:</term>
      <listitem><para> A structure kernel which contains bounding boxes, weights, filter coefficients, center of filter, size of filter, orientation of filter</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>bboxes:</term>
      <listitem><para> bounding boxes that define the filter</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>weights:</term>
      <listitem><para> weights corresponding to each of the bbox</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
Integral kernel creates box filter which can be used with integral images.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
